 MBOMBELA – After more than a month the carcasses of dead animals were finally cleaned out of the fridge at the Nelspruit SPCA. According to Nelspruit SPCA chairman, Lize Pienaar, representatives from the City of Mbombela Local Municipality came to clean out the fridges on Thursday. ALSO READ: Municipality turns back as animal bodies pile up at the SPCA Ward councillor, Tersia Marshall pledged her allegiance to the organisation last week and said she would ensure that the pound agreement between the SPCA and the municipality be enforced. The Nelspruit SPCA, along with the branches in Barberton and White River, were awarded pound status in August last year. ALSO READ: Dogs starved for eight months after owner moves